From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Carmine Scarpitta <cscarpit@cisco.com>
Subject: [PATCH] zebra: Don't skip kernel routes uninstall

Remove the RIB_KERNEL_ROUTE guard on the delete path in rib_process()
so that kernel route deletions are propagated to dataplane providers
(FPM), restoring symmetry with the add path.

Upstream: https://github.com/FRRouting/frr/issues/19637

Signed-off-by: Carmine Scarpitta <cscarpit@cisco.com>
---
 zebra/zebra_rib.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/zebra/zebra_rib.c b/zebra/zebra_rib.c
index 2b09fa9a9..a56dc893f 100644
--- a/zebra/zebra_rib.c
+++ b/zebra/zebra_rib.c
@@ -1498,7 +1498,7 @@ static void rib_process(struct route_node *rn)
 		rib_process_update_fib(zvrf, rn, old_fib, new_fib);
 	else if (new_fib)
 		rib_process_add_fib(zvrf, rn, new_fib);
-	else if (old_fib && !RIB_KERNEL_ROUTE(old_fib))
+	else if (old_fib)
 		rib_process_del_fib(zvrf, rn, old_fib);
 
 	/* Remove all RE entries queued for removal */
